webpackJsonp([0xcbb330fdc78],{1977:function(o,t){o.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Justin Ball",author:"Justin Ball"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/jbasdf/projects/justinball/src/posts/2013-02-20-font-awesome-or-any-other-webfont-in-production/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>If you are using <a href="http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/">Twitter Bootstrap</a> then it\'s likely you\'re also using <a href="http://fortawesome.github.com/Font-Awesome/">Font Awesome</a>. If not you need to check it out.</p>\n<p>We ran into a problem after deploying to production that we didn\'t observe in development - namely that none of the Font Awesome icons would show up under Firefox. <a href="http://serverfault.com/questions/186965/how-can-i-make-nginx-support-font-face-formats-and-allow-access-control-allow-o">Turns you you need to configure your server to send the proper headers and allow cross domain requests</a>. Also check out <a href="http://www.red-team-design.com/firefox-doesnt-allow-cross-domain-fonts-by-default">Firefox doesn\'t allow cross domain fonts</a>.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Font Awesome (or any other webfont in production)",date:"February 20, 2013",imageUrl:null,structuredHtml:null,image:null}}},pathContext:{}}}});
